# Data for: Modeling emergence pattern of five weed species as impacted by cereal rye cover crop

# Description of the data and file structure
This dataset contains field, and modeling output ("STM2 Output") collected from 2021–2023 at the University of Minnesota Rosemount Research and Outreach Center (RROC) in Rosemount, Minnesota. The study evaluated the effects of cereal rye cover crop on the emergence dynamics of commonly found weeds in soybean production systems in the US Upper Midwest.

#STM2 Output
Soil Temperature and Moisture Model (STM2) was used for this study to simiulate soil microclimate conditions in treatments with and without cover crop:
https://www.ars.usda.gov/research/software/download/?softwareid=209&modecode=50-60-05-00

Input parameters for this model in this study is included in the materials and methods.

Temperature data, collected from a weather station located at the Rosemount Research and Outreach Center (Station ID: 217107), was used to generate the STM2 output:
https://www.dnr.state.mn.us/climate/historical/daily-data.html?sid=217107&sname=ROSEMOUNT%20RESEARCH%20AND%20OUTREACH%20CENTER&sdate=por&edate=por

There are four tabs which separates data for treatments in cover crops and no cover crops for each year of data collection (2022 and 2023).

#Variables
Day (decimal day): Data output was set to hourly (set of 24 data points for each day)
Node Temp(C) 2.00 cm: Soil temperature (C) at 2.00 cm depth
Node Theta(cm3/cm3 vol) 2.00 cm: Soil moisture (cm3/cm3 vol) at 2.00 cm depth 
Node SMP(kPa) 2.00 cm: Soil moisture (kPa) at 2.00 cm depth

#Light Data (Red to Far Red Ratio)
Red:far-red (R:FR) ratio was measured in both cover crop and no-cover crop treatments at three randomly selected locations within each treatment.

#Variables
Year: Year of data collection
Sampling Date: Day of data collection
No Cover Crop_1: Sample 1 for R:FR value in no cover crop treatments
No Cover Crop_2: Sample 2 for R:FR value in no cover crop treatments
No Cover Crop_3: Sample 3 for R:FR value in no cover crop treatments
No Cover Crop_Avg: Average of three samples for R:FR value in no cover crop treatments
Cover Crop_1: Sample 1 for R:FR value in cover crop treatments
Cover Crop_2: Sample 2 for R:FR value in cover crop treatments
Cover Crop_3: Sample 3 for R:FR value in cover crop treatments
Cover Crop_Avg: Average of three samples for R:FR value in cover crop treatments
Percent Reduction: R:FR percent reduction from no cover crop treatments to cover crop treatments

#Cumulative Emergence Data
Weed seedling emergence was monitored and counted throughout the entire emergence period (from first observation to final emergence) within fixed plots.

#Variables
Year: Year of data collection
Sampling Date: Day of data collection
Plot: Fixed field plot monitored repeatedly throughout the weed emergence period.
Replication: Experimental replicate identifier (three replications per species)
Weed Species: Target weed species evaluated in the study (five total species)
Day of Year:Sequential day of the calendar year (e.g., 1 = January 1)
Emergence Count: Number of newly emerged seedlings recorded on a given sampling date (plants m⁻²)
Cumulative Emergence: Total number of emerged seedlings recorded from the start of monitoring up to and including the given sampling date (plants m⁻²)
Percent Cumulative Emergence: Cumulative emergence expressed as a percentage of the total seasonal emergence for that species, plot, and year (%).
Hydrothermal Time: Accumulated hydrothermal time calculated from soil temperature and matric potential outputs generated by the STM2 model.

#Code/Software
Microsoft Excel or another spreadsheet software is needed to view this data.
